[[File:Md-12_Missile_Defence_Satellite.jpg|thumb|right|200px|An Md-12 Missile Defense Satellite.]]

The '''Md-12 missile defense satellite''' was an armed space platform developed by the [[Corporate Sector Authority/Legends|Corporate Sector Authority]] for the defense of orbital installations and space stations.

The Md-12 was equipped with twin missile pods and internal magazines that fired large volleys of [[Concussion missile/Legends|concussion missiles]] at a target. The missiles were moderately powerful and well-suited for attacking frigates or fighters due to the fact that they could easily penetrate energy shields.

The missile platform was designed for construction on a pre-developed, multi-purpose satellite base, similar to the the [[Ld-12 laser defense satellite platform]].

